t can see them with \\\"opens.\\\" The developer mentioned we shouldn't edit the metadata because Forge takes care of it. The tests seem to generate this metadata through the agent on the JVM with add-opens, so I wonder if the native part will have reflect config for those JDK fields. But wouldn't the user code filter only focus on user code? Let me investigate that filter further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZSHGopkpsaQhKKNHTTUowlda|fc_0317bfbd632d8e47016a0de9cc8524819da19386a78a023e88", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 200}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/user-code-filter.json\",\"limit\":200}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1327, "output": 1881, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52360, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779296685229, "responseId": "resp_0317bfbd632d8e47016a0de9af2004819db78e7a9d55e9de31"}}
